'''Flare sticks''', also known as '''ground flares''', were small pyrotechnic devices used for illumination and signalling. Unscrewing a [[Flare/Legends|flare]] stick would activate the chemicals stored within. The reaction of those chemicals resulted in the emanation of a bright glow from the flare stick. A flare stick could be deactivated and saved for later use by screwing the two ends back together.

